  "prompt": "Who is the most educated president in the world ?",
  "response": "Determining the \"most educated\" president in the world can be subjective, as it depends on how one defines \"education.\" For example, some might consider the number of degrees earned, the prestige of institutions attended, or the breadth of academic achievements.\n\nOne president often cited as highly educated is **Dr. Jos\u00e9 Ramos-Horta**, who served as the President of East Timor (Timor-Leste). He holds a master's degree in Peace Studies from Antioch University and has received honorary doctorates from several universities worldwide. Ramos-Horta is also a Nobel Peace Prize laureate (1996) for his efforts in promoting peace in East Timor.\n\nAnother notable example is **Dr. A. P. J. Abdul Kalam**, former President of India, who was an aerospace engineer and a key figure in India's space and missile programs. He held honorary doctorates from over 40 universities and institutions and was widely regarded as the \"People's President\" for his contributions to science and education.\n\nIn the United States, **Woodrow Wilson** is often regarded as one of the most educated presidents. He earned a Ph.D. in Political Science from Johns Hopkins University and was the only U.S. president to hold a doctorate.\n\nUltimately, the title of \"most educated\" can vary based on the criteria used, but these leaders stand out for their significant academic and intellectual achievements.",
